00:12:53.160 --> 00:12:58.120
Since 2005, ITN has been a
shareholder of the Espresso Group

00:12:58.120 --> 00:13:00.780
that provides digital
content to primary schools

00:13:00.780 --> 00:13:04.510
in the UK and also international.

00:13:04.510 --> 00:13:09.170
Digitization dictated that we adapt
our cataloguing practices to focus

00:13:09.170 --> 00:13:12.120
on metadata frameworks and
standards and begin thinking

00:13:12.120 --> 00:13:16.050
about the semantic web and
the opportunities it offers.

00:13:16.050 --> 00:13:20.170
The generation of metadata is
no longer solely in our domain.

00:13:20.170 --> 00:13:22.100
We are gradually becoming dependent

00:13:22.100 --> 00:13:25.020
on metadata generated
by other sources.

00:13:25.020 --> 00:13:30.590
Annemieke de Jong wrote already in
2007 that more and more metadata

00:13:30.590 --> 00:13:35.850
on the materials that we maintain
