outside of our research and control.

00:13:40.970 --> 00:13:44.690
This concerns metadata that
is derived automatically,

00:13:44.690 --> 00:13:48.140
but also metadata that
is put in by humans.

00:13:48.140 --> 00:13:51.820
De Jong predicted that
professional cataloguers may feel

00:13:51.820 --> 00:13:55.110
that these developments will
cause them to lose a bit

00:13:55.110 --> 00:13:58.110
of their expertise
exclusiveness and that they will

00:13:58.110 --> 00:14:02.460
to have share their job, their
expertise with nonexperts.

00:14:02.460 --> 00:14:07.450
They're bound to have to develop a
few more important new focuses too

00:14:07.450 --> 00:14:09.600
like maintaining the
metadata quality

00:14:09.600 --> 00:14:13.370
in the production environment doing
quality checks, advocate the use

00:14:13.370 --> 00:14:16.700
